1
00:00:12,916 --> 00:00:15,333
[window rattling]

2
00:00:15,416 --> 00:00:17,833
[fire crackling]

3
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:22,916
[MARLYA] I had parents,
But I never knew them.

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,416
[humming]

5
00:00:32,708 --> 00:00:34,708
[wood cracking]

6
00:00:36,708 --> 00:00:39,833
Monika.
We'll need more wood.

7
00:00:42,916 --> 00:00:45,041
Hmm.

8
00:00:45,125 --> 00:00:46,916
[grunts]

9
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,833
Oh!

10
00:00:48,916 --> 00:00:51,416
Let me! I'll get it!

11
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:54,333
[humming continues]

12
00:00:54,416 --> 00:00:56,416
[wind whistling]

13
00:00:58,083 --> 00:00:59,375
Hmm.

14
00:00:59,458 --> 00:01:03,333
[GIRLS laughing]

15
00:01:03,416 --> 00:01:05,291
[VILLAGE GIRL 1]
It's freezing out.

16
00:01:05,375 --> 00:01:07,500
[VILLAGE GIRL 2] Sure is.
So, what should we do today?

17
00:01:07,583 --> 00:01:09,291
Warm up
Ugh!

18
00:01:09,375 --> 00:01:13,000
-Direct hit!
-[BOYS laughing]

19
00:01:13,083 --> 00:01:15,333
Jerks!

20
00:01:15,416 --> 00:01:16,541
[ALL gasp]

21
00:01:18,875 --> 00:01:21,083
[GIRLS giggling]

22
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:26,291
[VERONICA] My life
used to be full of light.

23
00:01:32,208 --> 00:01:34,125
[MARLYA]
My father's gone now.

24
00:01:34,208 --> 00:01:36,041
I know he's dead.

25
00:01:36,125 --> 00:01:37,791
But was it my fault?

26
00:01:39,125 --> 00:01:41,166
[JURGEN]
Some say it was.

27
00:01:41,250 --> 00:01:42,750
What about my mother?

28
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:44,333
You're too young
to realize this,

29
00:01:44,416 --> 00:01:47,708
but she's not the only woman
to die in childbirth.

30
00:01:48,916 --> 00:01:50,666
It's just...

31
00:01:50,750 --> 00:01:53,750
Am I a little disaster
like everyone says?

32
00:01:53,833 --> 00:01:56,583
♪

33
00:02:02,875 --> 00:02:05,541
[whimpers]

34
00:02:16,250 --> 00:02:18,958
[VERONICA]
I lost everything in this life.

35
00:02:20,541 --> 00:02:22,916
No. It was taken from me.

36
00:02:29,375 --> 00:02:31,250
♪

37
00:02:36,666 --> 00:02:40,041
[MARLYA] There's only
one person I want to see.

38
00:02:45,375 --> 00:02:46,958
I have a good feeling
this Ray Dawn

39
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:48,625
is going to make
an excellent duke.

40
00:02:48,708 --> 00:02:51,000
Seems like a decent man.

41
00:02:51,083 --> 00:02:53,166
Be sure to take care of
yourself, madam.

42
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:54,500
You matter.

43
00:02:54,583 --> 00:02:56,958
Such kind-hearted sentiments,

44
00:02:57,041 --> 00:02:59,416
and from our new king,
no less.

45
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:01,958
You honor me,
but I am not a king.

46
00:03:02,041 --> 00:03:03,625
-There's a gun!
-Oh!

47
00:03:03,708 --> 00:03:05,583
-She's armed!
-Guard the duke!

48
00:03:05,666 --> 00:03:07,125
[ALL gasping]

49
00:03:07,208 --> 00:03:10,000
VERONICA] Even if I can never
get back what was taken.

50
00:03:11,416 --> 00:03:13,458
-Ray Dawn!
-Drop the gun now!

51
00:03:19,541 --> 00:03:21,125
[VERONICA]
Why did you do it?

52
00:03:22,583 --> 00:03:24,500
It's your fault. All of it!

53
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,375
[energy surging]

54
00:03:29,458 --> 00:03:30,750
[gasps]

55
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:36,375
♪

56
00:03:51,250 --> 00:03:53,250
[MARLYA]
Where did you go?

57
00:03:55,041 --> 00:03:57,041
♪

58
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:05,541
[VERONICA] I have to take back
as much as I lost.

59
00:04:06,833 --> 00:04:08,791
Because I'm still empty inside.

60
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:15,541
[crying]

61
00:04:28,208 --> 00:04:30,375
[MARLYA]
Where are you, Ver?

62
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,375
[glass shattering]

63
00:06:16,291 --> 00:06:17,250
Oh!

64
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:19,541
[glass falling]

65
00:06:19,625 --> 00:06:21,291
[gasps]

66
00:06:21,375 --> 00:06:22,791
[MARLYA]
Ver!

67
00:06:25,416 --> 00:06:28,416
Welcome. You're a little early
for the unveiling.

68
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:31,333
Or do you intend to prevent me
from completing my art?

69
00:06:31,416 --> 00:06:33,541
Don't make me laugh.
What art?

70
00:06:33,625 --> 00:06:35,666
[grunting]

71
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:43,375
-[JONATHAN] Here!
-On your left!

72
00:06:46,791 --> 00:06:48,208
Ah!

73
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,625
[lick lips]

74
00:06:52,958 --> 00:06:54,625
[JONATHAN]
Jenny!

75
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:57,375
[roaring]

76
00:06:57,458 --> 00:06:59,416
He has a fairy.

77
00:07:03,166 --> 00:07:04,416
[JONATHAN]
Ha, ha!

78
00:07:07,458 --> 00:07:08,916
[blades ringing]

79
00:07:12,875 --> 00:07:14,250
[quiet laughter]

80
00:07:16,958 --> 00:07:19,291
[JONATHAN]
Papa, behold.

81
00:07:19,375 --> 00:07:22,375
Is this not
the fairy you envisioned?

82
00:07:22,458 --> 00:07:26,000
Ah, I can hear
Mama's song in my head.

83
00:07:26,083 --> 00:07:27,625
[roaring]

84
00:07:27,708 --> 00:07:29,416
He's sicker than I thought.

85
00:07:32,875 --> 00:07:34,208
[sighs]

86
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:38,916
Your move.

87
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,708
[roaring]

88
00:07:44,541 --> 00:07:45,916
[liquid bubbling]

89
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,666
Take this!

90
00:07:51,833 --> 00:07:53,416
[shouts]

91
00:07:58,208 --> 00:08:01,458
I was expecting more of a fight!
Turns out you're nothing!

92
00:08:01,541 --> 00:08:03,125
[grunting]

93
00:08:06,125 --> 00:08:09,041
She's good.
Really good.

94
00:08:13,166 --> 00:08:14,291
Hello!

95
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:19,000
[blades ringing]

96
00:08:22,666 --> 00:08:23,958
[laughs]

97
00:08:26,541 --> 00:08:27,833
Please. Allow me.

98
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:30,916
[explosion]

99
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,000
♪

100
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:39,166
[flames whoosh]

101
00:08:39,250 --> 00:08:41,625
You specialize in parlor tricks?

102
00:08:41,708 --> 00:08:43,333
This, my dear, is art!

103
00:08:43,416 --> 00:08:45,333
But a commoner
like you wouldn't know.

104
00:08:45,416 --> 00:08:47,291
[laughing]

105
00:08:48,375 --> 00:08:51,416
How can I be so powerless?

106
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:54,750
No. That's the old me.
I have to fight!

107
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,125
[shouting]

108
00:08:58,375 --> 00:08:59,333
Aah!

109
00:09:03,666 --> 00:09:04,958
[chuckles]
Aah!

110
00:09:09,458 --> 00:09:10,416
Ha!

111
00:09:17,208 --> 00:09:18,958
[grunting]

112
00:09:20,916 --> 00:09:22,416
Really?

113
00:09:24,083 --> 00:09:25,500
[blade drops]

114
00:09:26,916 --> 00:09:28,750
[shouting]

115
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:37,166
-[liquid bubbling]
-Hmm?

116
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:40,583
Quit screwing around
and attack!

117
00:09:42,958 --> 00:09:44,875
[roaring]

118
00:09:47,750 --> 00:09:48,916
[panting]

119
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:55,791
Hmm.

120
00:09:55,875 --> 00:10:01,416
[vocalizing]

121
00:10:08,916 --> 00:10:10,791
[continues vocalizing]

122
00:10:15,791 --> 00:10:17,541
[rumbling]

123
00:10:20,125 --> 00:10:21,291
[scoffs]

124
00:10:21,375 --> 00:10:23,208
[flame lights]

125
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:32,541
[MARLYA]
I'm not the same person.

126
00:10:32,625 --> 00:10:34,083
I'll prove it!

127
00:10:34,166 --> 00:10:36,208
[screaming]

128
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:39,416
Ah! What beauty.

129
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:41,375
Get back!
Take cover, Ver!

130
00:10:43,625 --> 00:10:45,541
♪

131
00:10:49,791 --> 00:10:50,750
[gasps]

132
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:56,708
♪

133
00:10:56,791 --> 00:10:59,708
[JONATHAN]
Stunning. Truly stunning!

134
00:11:08,333 --> 00:11:09,750
We're safe.

135
00:11:12,291 --> 00:11:13,625
[VERONICA]
Quickly.

136
00:11:18,083 --> 00:11:19,500
[gunshot]

137
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:21,958
[gunshot]

138
00:11:22,041 --> 00:11:23,041
[roaring]

139
00:11:26,541 --> 00:11:27,875
You damned mutt.

140
00:11:27,958 --> 00:11:29,166
♪

141
00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:34,250
Hi.

142
00:11:37,208 --> 00:11:38,375
[growls]

143
00:11:44,583 --> 00:11:46,208
Go ahead.

144
00:11:47,375 --> 00:11:48,750
Thank a lot,
Bitter Sweet.

145
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:51,083
This is one hell of a job
you dropped in my lap.

146
00:11:54,125 --> 00:11:55,458
Hey! Stop!

147
00:11:58,250 --> 00:12:00,416
I didn't expect that.

148
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:03,708
[PATTY laughing]

149
00:12:03,791 --> 00:12:05,416
Until next time!

150
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,000
[panting]

151
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:17,750
[flames crackling]

152
00:12:20,958 --> 00:12:22,416
What's wrong?

153
00:12:24,958 --> 00:12:27,041
Thank you so much.

154
00:12:27,125 --> 00:12:28,458
For saving me.

155
00:12:31,541 --> 00:12:33,166
We both made it.

156
00:12:33,250 --> 00:12:35,000
I had no idea where you were,

157
00:12:35,083 --> 00:12:37,208
but I knew for certain
you were safe.

158
00:12:37,291 --> 00:12:39,875
After all, I survived.

159
00:12:39,958 --> 00:12:41,208
Yeah, safe.

160
00:12:41,291 --> 00:12:44,041
The assassination attempt
on Ray Dawn.

161
00:12:44,125 --> 00:12:46,125
That was you, right?

162
00:12:46,208 --> 00:12:48,375
Only a minor setback.

163
00:12:48,458 --> 00:12:51,291
What do you mean?
You haven't given up yet?

164
00:12:51,375 --> 00:12:53,791
You're not seriously
going to try again.

165
00:12:56,083 --> 00:12:58,541
Don't do it, Ver!
Killing him won't change any--

166
00:12:58,625 --> 00:12:59,666
ah!

167
00:13:01,125 --> 00:13:04,666
Dear Mama,
let me hear you sing.

168
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:09,125
Papa, aren't you proud of how
well your little boy can paint?

169
00:13:09,208 --> 00:13:11,291
He's still alive. No way.

170
00:13:12,791 --> 00:13:13,875
[blade rings]

171
00:13:15,041 --> 00:13:16,208
Ah ha!

172
00:13:17,625 --> 00:13:18,875
[shouts]

173
00:13:24,083 --> 00:13:27,291
Ah, now that's real art!

174
00:13:28,958 --> 00:13:30,416
[shaky laughter]

175
00:13:33,958 --> 00:13:35,500
[laughter continues]

176
00:13:35,583 --> 00:13:36,666
Yes!

177
00:13:38,333 --> 00:13:39,958
[liquid squelches]

178
00:13:44,458 --> 00:13:45,958
[breathing shakily]

179
00:13:52,166 --> 00:13:53,666
Please stay!

180
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:55,208
[VERONICA]
I just wanted to tell you.

181
00:13:56,541 --> 00:13:58,291
Don't try to find me.

182
00:13:58,375 --> 00:14:01,500
-It wouldn't end well.
-Why?

183
00:14:01,583 --> 00:14:03,083
[VERONICA]
Like I said,

184
00:14:03,166 --> 00:14:05,541
the Veronica Thorn
you knew is dead.

185
00:14:05,625 --> 00:14:07,250
Accept it.

186
00:14:13,958 --> 00:14:14,958
[gasps]

187
00:14:17,916 --> 00:14:20,125
[flames whooshing]

188
00:14:20,208 --> 00:14:22,791
Ver!

189
00:14:24,416 --> 00:14:25,750
[metal scraping]

190
00:14:27,083 --> 00:14:28,083
[grunts]

191
00:14:30,041 --> 00:14:31,000
Huh?

192
00:14:49,916 --> 00:14:51,333
[footsteps approaching]

193
00:14:51,416 --> 00:14:52,541
[WOLF]
Your Grace.

194
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:54,541
Taking your leave?

195
00:14:54,625 --> 00:14:55,916
[WOLF]
I am.

196
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,916
Hmm.
We should expect things

197
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,291
to start heating up
around here.

198
00:15:00,375 --> 00:15:02,250
[WOLF]
I'll do whatever I can.

199
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:05,375
[DIESE]
One moment, Wolfran.

200
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:09,208
What is your purpose
for living?

201
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:13,750
I can't think of any other way
I'm supposed to exist.

202
00:15:13,833 --> 00:15:15,333
[laughing]

203
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,708
[DIESE]
Nor can I.

204
00:15:25,625 --> 00:15:27,291
♪

205
00:15:28,791 --> 00:15:31,166
-Ow! It hurts.
-[whimpers]

206
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:35,041
[ELENOA] There's a chance
it'll leave a scar.

207
00:15:35,125 --> 00:15:36,291
[MARLYA]
I'm lucky.

208
00:15:36,375 --> 00:15:37,708
It could've been worse.

209
00:15:37,791 --> 00:15:40,041
And where was Free
during all of this?

210
00:15:40,125 --> 00:15:41,875
He's not responsible
for my safety.

211
00:15:41,958 --> 00:15:43,750
Regardless, he is still a man.

212
00:15:43,833 --> 00:15:45,541
He should've protected you.

213
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:50,125
To be honest, the thought
never crossed my mind.

214
00:15:50,208 --> 00:15:52,041
Sure, it didn't.

215
00:15:52,125 --> 00:15:53,541
Oh! Wait, hang on.

216
00:15:58,625 --> 00:15:59,625
Hmmm.

217
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:08,416
-[ELENOA] You check out.
-[MARLYA sighs]

218
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:11,166
Is there anything
you wanted to ask me about?

219
00:16:11,250 --> 00:16:12,333
[MARLYA]
Mmm, no.

220
00:16:12,416 --> 00:16:14,291
But I'll let you know
if there is.

221
00:16:21,708 --> 00:16:22,916
[sighs]

222
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:29,958
Fairy possession, huh?

223
00:16:35,458 --> 00:16:37,291
♪

224
00:16:37,375 --> 00:16:38,708
[door opens]

225
00:16:38,791 --> 00:16:39,916
We have arrived!

226
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,375
Hold the applause!

227
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:43,208
Here comes that rookie.

228
00:16:43,291 --> 00:16:45,125
He's still a loud mouth,
it seems.

229
00:16:45,208 --> 00:16:47,375
That's an understatement.

230
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:51,625
Found us a table!
Over here, Marlya!

231
00:16:51,708 --> 00:16:53,666
Come on!
You can sit next to me!

232
00:16:53,750 --> 00:16:56,291
Could he be any louder?

233
00:16:56,375 --> 00:16:57,291
After you.

234
00:16:57,375 --> 00:16:59,000
Oh, thank you.

235
00:17:03,125 --> 00:17:04,291
[whistles]

236
00:17:06,541 --> 00:17:08,500
[chuckles] Oh!

237
00:17:08,583 --> 00:17:09,958
Actually, sir...

238
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:12,500
You going to sit down or what?

239
00:17:12,583 --> 00:17:14,291
Yeah. Sure.

240
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:17,291
Who are those men at the bar?

241
00:17:17,375 --> 00:17:18,875
You mean the three wolves?

242
00:17:18,958 --> 00:17:21,541
[MARLYA] Do they have
some sort connection with us?

243
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:23,000
[SERGE]
Ha. You just said “us.”

244
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:24,208
Which means
you consider yourself

245
00:17:24,291 --> 00:17:25,916
officially one of the gang.

246
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,458
[MARLYA]
I just thought avoiding

247
00:17:27,541 --> 00:17:29,541
saying our group's name
was for the best.

248
00:17:29,625 --> 00:17:32,166
[KLARA] It won't be
a problem in this pub.

249
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:35,166
It's one of our favorite
haunts since it's nearby.

250
00:17:35,250 --> 00:17:37,708
To answer your question,
those three are regulars here.

251
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:40,041
[GONZALEZ] Correction.
We're outstanding regulars.

252
00:17:40,125 --> 00:17:43,250
I'll have you know for a fact,
I was a hero of the great war.

253
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:45,541
[SERGE]
That you were! See Gon here?

254
00:17:45,625 --> 00:17:48,291
During his military service,
he was captain.

255
00:17:48,375 --> 00:17:49,583
[MARLYA]
Really?

256
00:17:49,666 --> 00:17:51,041
I had the distinct honor

257
00:17:51,125 --> 00:17:52,500
of serving under his command.

258
00:17:52,583 --> 00:17:55,250
You wouldn't know,
but this one's a good soldier.

259
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:57,916
Wow.

260
00:17:58,916 --> 00:18:00,916
[train rumbling]

261
00:18:12,125 --> 00:18:13,833
[DIESE]
Ray Dawn.

262
00:18:15,750 --> 00:18:16,875
Hmm.

263
00:18:18,041 --> 00:18:22,041
History has only
one author: The victor.

264
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:25,291
[SERGE]
If I may have your attention!

265
00:18:25,375 --> 00:18:26,833
Even though it's late,
this get together

266
00:18:26,916 --> 00:18:29,083
is both a welcoming party
for Marlya.

267
00:18:29,166 --> 00:18:31,291
And to celebrate
the success of her mission!

268
00:18:31,375 --> 00:18:33,250
Cheers to Marlya!

269
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:34,875
[ALL]
Cheers!

270
00:18:36,583 --> 00:18:37,625
Ah!

271
00:18:37,708 --> 00:18:39,375
Needed that!

272
00:18:40,416 --> 00:18:43,083
[ELENOA]
Can I get another one over here?

273
00:18:43,166 --> 00:18:44,666
She downed that.

274
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:46,833
Permission to guess
what's eating at you, sir?

275
00:18:46,916 --> 00:18:48,500
Let me see.

276
00:18:48,583 --> 00:18:51,375
Is it because you were ambushed
by that Gui Carlin cleaner,

277
00:18:51,458 --> 00:18:52,791
and she managed to get away?

278
00:18:52,875 --> 00:18:54,375
[scoffs]

279
00:18:54,458 --> 00:18:55,875
[SERGE]
You should've taken me along.

280
00:18:55,958 --> 00:18:57,625
You know that
I'm a good luck charm.

281
00:18:57,708 --> 00:18:59,625
[FREE]
Yeah, right. Keep dreaming.

282
00:19:00,875 --> 00:19:02,333
Are you feeling up for this?

283
00:19:02,416 --> 00:19:05,208
You should take it easy,
since you're still recovering.

284
00:19:05,291 --> 00:19:07,791
It's not that at all.
I'm fine. Really.

285
00:19:07,875 --> 00:19:10,500
You wouldn't know it by
looking at her, but she's tough.

286
00:19:10,583 --> 00:19:13,166
I appreciate it, but are you
implying that I look weak?

287
00:19:13,250 --> 00:19:15,083
He thinks you're cute
and is too afraid to say it.

288
00:19:15,166 --> 00:19:17,375
I believe I said
exactly what I meant.

289
00:19:17,458 --> 00:19:21,458
Well. I have no reservations
admitting I think Marlya's cute.

290
00:19:21,541 --> 00:19:25,208
Just a little FYI.
He says that line with everyone.

291
00:19:25,291 --> 00:19:27,041
Yeah, I bet.

292
00:19:27,125 --> 00:19:29,041
Funny.
He never used it on me before.

293
00:19:29,125 --> 00:19:31,375
[SERGE] Only because
you exude different qualities!

294
00:19:31,458 --> 00:19:32,791
Like nobility and beauty!

295
00:19:32,875 --> 00:19:35,541
-And the director?
-Oh! Director Nein?

296
00:19:35,625 --> 00:19:38,625
Huh, I guess I kinda find her,
well, just between us--

297
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:41,791
[FREE]
So, Ozz, already moving on

298
00:19:41,875 --> 00:19:43,333
to the harder stuff?

299
00:19:43,416 --> 00:19:45,166
Didn't you invite the director?

300
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:46,666
Yeah, of course I did!

301
00:19:48,875 --> 00:19:51,041
She politely said
no way in hell.

302
00:19:51,125 --> 00:19:53,583
She has far more important
matters to attend to.

303
00:19:53,666 --> 00:19:56,166
Even so, you have to at least
extend an invitation

304
00:19:56,250 --> 00:19:57,916
or she might
take it personally.

305
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:01,375
Yeah. She can get that way.
Surprisingly.

306
00:20:01,458 --> 00:20:03,583
[KLARA] She's not
that kind of person at all.

307
00:20:03,666 --> 00:20:05,500
[FREE] You don't know
her true nature yet.

308
00:20:05,583 --> 00:20:08,625
-Believe me.
-Hate to disagree, but I do.

309
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,375
[SERGE]
Maybe you're not aware, Marlya,

310
00:20:10,458 --> 00:20:12,541
but Klara owes
the director her life.

311
00:20:12,625 --> 00:20:14,458
And I won't ever forget it.

312
00:20:14,541 --> 00:20:16,500
If she hadn't intervened
and saved me,

313
00:20:16,583 --> 00:20:18,458
I wouldn't be
sitting here right now.

314
00:20:21,333 --> 00:20:23,916
And he's moved on
to a second bottle.

315
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,958
Y'know, when you really
think about it,

316
00:20:26,041 --> 00:20:28,583
you could say I technically
owe her my life too.

317
00:20:28,666 --> 00:20:31,125
Only difference being
you begged her for yours.

318
00:20:31,208 --> 00:20:33,208
[SERGE] That's another way
to put it, I suppose.

319
00:20:33,291 --> 00:20:35,666
Bottom line,
the director's the greatest!

320
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:37,666
Three cheers for Nein Auler!

321
00:20:38,708 --> 00:20:40,583
Hey, everybody's got a history.

322
00:20:40,666 --> 00:20:43,375
No two are the same.
It's a universal truth.

323
00:20:44,625 --> 00:20:45,916
[sighs]

324
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:48,333
Are you already smashed
off your first drink?

325
00:20:48,416 --> 00:20:49,875
Oh, what do you know?

326
00:20:49,958 --> 00:20:51,583
[GONZALEZ]
I hope everyone's not.

327
00:20:51,666 --> 00:20:54,541
'Cause the night's young
and this one's on me!

328
00:20:54,625 --> 00:20:57,333
Gonzalez! A hero on
and off the battlefield!

329
00:20:57,416 --> 00:20:58,916
The anniversary is soon.

330
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,333
Time to celebrate
the end of the war.

331
00:21:01,416 --> 00:21:03,041
Do your best
to keep us safe.

332
00:21:03,125 --> 00:21:05,375
Will do! Hey, Steve!

333
00:21:05,458 --> 00:21:07,000
Bring us some more glasses!

334
00:21:07,083 --> 00:21:08,875
Yes, sir! Right away!

335
00:21:08,958 --> 00:21:10,333
Don't humor the kid.

336
00:21:10,416 --> 00:21:12,791
[FREE] And you,
stop ordering Steve around.

337
00:21:12,875 --> 00:21:14,250
Easy there, Ozz.

338
00:21:14,333 --> 00:21:15,625
[SERGE]
No kidding!

339
00:21:15,708 --> 00:21:17,958
This celebration's
supposed to be for Marlya!

340
00:21:18,041 --> 00:21:20,041
At least give us the chance
to catch up to you.

341
00:21:20,125 --> 00:21:22,166
Steve! We're gonna need
those glasses, fast!

342
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:23,500
[STEVE]
Sir, yes sir!

343
00:21:23,583 --> 00:21:25,541
[FREE]
Serge! What did I just say?

344
00:21:25,625 --> 00:21:27,708
[SERGE] Aw, come on!
He misses being a soldier!

345
00:21:27,791 --> 00:21:29,208
[FREE]
Pace yourself or your night's

346
00:21:29,291 --> 00:21:30,583
going to be over too soon.

347
00:21:30,666 --> 00:21:31,791
[SERGE]
We'll see.

348
00:21:31,875 --> 00:21:34,500
♪

349
00:23:05,416 --> 00:23:08,416
[VERONICA humming]

350
00:23:39,208 --> 00:23:40,625
[MARLYA]
Improved artificial fairies.

351
00:23:40,708 --> 00:23:42,125
[NEIN] We received info
from a certain source

352
00:23:42,208 --> 00:23:43,416
about the Black Fairy Tome.

353
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:44,833
[KLARA]
We’re in pursuit of a suspect.

354
00:23:44,916 --> 00:23:46,083
[BUZ] You'll need to sweeten
the deal somehow.

355
00:23:46,166 --> 00:23:48,458
My little Dorothea bitches.

